{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πύργος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>tower</b>, especially such as were attached to the walls of a city, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.219, +others, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 242, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.74, +others, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.17, +others, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.99.9, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>city walls</b> or <b>ramparts with their towers</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.338, 437; in _sing._, ἧντ᾽ ἐπὶ πύργῳ 3.153, compare 22.447; πόλιος ἣν πέρι πύργος ὑψηλός 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.262; πέριξ δὲ πύργος εἶχ᾽ ἔτι πτόλιν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1209; πύργους ἐπὶ τῶν γεφυρῶν ἐπιστῆσαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 116a. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> <b>movable tower</b> for storming towns, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.1.53, 6.2.18; π. ὑπότροχοι 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 42.3. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__c</b></Level4> <b>tower</b> on the back of war-elephants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Tactica” 2.4. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__d</b></Level4> Ζανὸς π., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Pythagoras Philosophus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] name for the central fire of the universe, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 204. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>tower of defence</b>, τοῖος.. σφιν π. ἀπώλεο, of Ajax, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.556; ἄνδρες πόλιος π. ἀρεύϊος 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 1a.10; παῖς ἄρσην πατέρ᾽ ἔχει π. μέγαν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 311, compare “Med.” 390; ἅπας μοι π. Ἑλλήνων πατρίς “Tragica Adespota” 392 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θανάτων δ᾽ ἐμᾷ χώρᾳ π. ἀνέστα <b>a tower of defence from</b> deaths, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1201 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>the part of a house</b> (probably a separate building) <b>in which the women lived and worked</b>, αἱ ἄλλαι θεράπαιναι ἐν τῷ π. ἦσαν, οὗπερ διαιτῶνται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 47.56; especially if unmarried, as 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] in her <b>tower</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Musaeus Epicus 32, 187, compare 3rd c.AD: Philostratus Junior Sophista “Imagines” 1 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; of the <b>workman's hut</b> of Timon the misanthrope (which also became his tomb,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tim.” 42), 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 1.30.4, compare “Anthologia Graeca” 7.402 (Antip.)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>outbuildings</b>, especially if used in industry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Isa.5.2, LXX.Mic.4.8, “PStrassb.” 110.6 (3rd c.BC), “BGU” 1194.9 (2nd c.BC), 650.8 (1st c.AD), “POxy.” 243.15 (1st c.AD), NT.Mark.12.1, NT.Luke.14.28, “PGiss.” 67.16 (2nd c.AD), “IG” 22.2776.65 (2nd c.AD)\">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>]; π. ἐν ᾧ βαφεῖον καὶ ἕτερα χρηστήρια [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 2.371.3 (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>part of an army drawn up in close order, column</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.334, 347. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> at Teos, a division of the people, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “CIG” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” 3064,3081, +others \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>dice-box,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 9.482.24 (6th c.AD: Agathias Historicus et Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]; cf. Latin <i>pyrgus.</i>","strongNumber":"G4444","accentedUnicode":"πύργος","shortDef":"tower, watchtower","mediumDef":"tower, watchtower <br /><b>a tower,</b> <ref='Mat.21.33'>Mt. 21:33</ref>; <ref='Mrk.12.1'>Mk. 12:1</ref>; <ref='Luk.13.4'>Lk. 13:4</ref>; <i>generically</i> <b>a castle, palace,</b> <ref='Luk.14.28'>Lk. 14:28</ref>*","stepGloss":"tower","stepTransliteration":"purgos","count":4,"_es_Definition":"torre, atalaya","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (瞭望用的) 塔<br>2) (塔型建築) 農莊 (路 14:28)","_zh_Definition":"1) (瞭望用的) 塔<br>2) (塔型建筑) 农庄 (路 14:28)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"tháp; tháp canh.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一座樓","_es_Gloss":"torre","_zh_Gloss":"一座楼"}]}